    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. CARTWRIGHT:H.R. 2130.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section VIII which states ``The Congress shallhave power to lay and collect taxes, duties, imposts andexcises, to pay the debts and provide for the common defenseand general welfare of the United States; but all duties,imposts and excises shall be uniform throughout the UnitedStates;''Most recently the Supreme Court has held that Article I,Section VIII gives Congress a plenary power to impose taxesand to spend money for the general welfare subject almostentirely to Congress's own discretion.[Page H2956]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
